  "source_id": "bph",
  "name": "BPH - Comprehensive Provider Query (Multi-Resource, Male, Age 40+)",
  "description": "Provider-level query identifying all BPH patients across the system using multi-resource evidence: Condition (BPH dx), MedicationRequest (alpha-blockers/5-ARI), Procedure (TURP). Restricted to males age 40+ via PatientFilters. Some patients have only meds (Path C — empirical alpha-blocker therapy without coded BPH dx).",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete BPH patient population for a urology quality initiative. Restrict to male patients age 40 and older. Some patients have a coded BPH diagnosis on their problem list. Others were started on alpha-blockers (tamsulosin, terazosin) or 5-alpha-reductase inhibitors (finasteride) for empirical lower urinary tract symptom management without ever getting a formal BPH diagnosis. A subset has undergone TURP (transurethral resection of the prostate). Please run multiple FHIR queries to capture the complete population — diagnosis, medications, and procedures — and union the patient sets.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all male patients with BPH.",
    "broad": "Find all male patients age 40+ with BPH — by diagnosis, BPH-class medications (alpha-blockers, 5-ARI), or TURP surgery. Run multiple queries and union the patients.",
    "expert": "Run three queries restricted to male patients age 40+. (1) Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|266569009&patient.birthdate=le1986-04-28&patient.gender=male — BPH dx. (2) MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|77492,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|25025,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|37798&patient.birthdate=le1986-04-28&patient.gender=male — BPH meds. (3) Procedure?code=http://snomed.info/sct|90199006&patient.birthdate=le1986-04-28&patient.gender=male — TURP. Union the patient IDs."
  },
